window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From Mark Greaney, the </b><b><i>New York Times</i></b><b> best-selling author of </b><b><i>Mission Critical</i></b><b> and a coauthor of Tom Clancy's Jack Ryan novels, comes another high-stakes thriller featuring the world's most dangerous assassin: the Gray Man.</b></p> <p>While on a mission to Croatia, Court Gentry uncovers a human trafficking operation. The trail leads from the Balkans all the way back to Hollywood.</p> <p>Court is determined to shut it down, but his CIA handlers have other plans. The criminal ringleader has actionable intelligence about a potentially devastating terrorist attack on the US. The CIA won't move until they have that intel. It's a moral balancing act with Court at the pivot point.</p>"; 
